2026-02-20 12:35:01 - INFO - 716 -{"tools": [], "type": "LLMCall", "messages": [{"content": "Travel Planner: Create day-by-day itinerary with activities, hotel options (budget/mid/luxury + prices), and budget breakdown (accommodation, food, transport, attractions, total).", "role": "system"}, {"role": "user", "name": "user", "content": "I want to two day trip to goa with the budget of 50000. Can you help me plan it?"}], "response": {"id": "chatcmpl-4193bfdd-ee34-4cd9-8009-c87026948196", "choices": [{"finish_reason": "stop", "index": 0, "logprobs": null, "message": {"content": "## 2\u2011Day Goa Getaway \u2013\u202f\u20b9\u202f50\u202f000 (INR) Budget  \n*(All prices are approximate, per person, and shown in Indian Rupees)*  \n\n| Category | What\u2019s Included | Approx. Cost (per person) |\n|----------|----------------|---------------------------|\n| **Flights / Train** | Round\u2011trip (Mumbai \u2194 Goa) \u2013 low\u2011cost airline or AC\u2011chair\u2011car train | **\u20b9\u202f6\u202f000 \u2013 9\u202f000** |\n| **Airport\u2011/Rail\u2011to\u2011Hotel Transfer** | Pre\u2011booked taxi / app\u2011cab (\u224830\u202fkm) | **\u20b9\u202f800 \u2013 1\u202f200** |\n| **Local Transport** | 2\u2011day scooter rental (incl. fuel) or 2\u2011day Uber/Taxi budget | **\u20b9\u202f800 \u2013 1\u202f200** |\n| **Accommodation** | See three hotel tiers below (2 nights) | **\u20b9\u202f4\u202f000 \u2013 40\u202f000** |\n| **Food & Drinks** | Breakfast, lunch, dinner + 2\u20113 drinks/snacks per day | **\u20b9\u202f2\u202f500 \u2013 7\u202f500** |\n| **Attractions & Activities** | Beach entry, entry fees, water\u2011sports, entry to forts/museums, night\u2011life entry | **\u20b9\u202f2\u202f000 \u2013 5\u202f000** |\n| **Miscellaneous** | Souvenirs, tips, emergency cash | **\u20b9\u202f500 \u2013 1\u202f000** |\n| **Total** |  | **\u20b9\u202f16\u202f600 \u2013 64\u202f900** |\n\n> **Bottom line:** Even the most luxurious option (\u20b9\u202f40\u202f000 for a 5\u2011star stay) stays well under the \u20b9\u202f50\u202f000 ceiling, leaving plenty of room for food, activities and a little shopping. Below you\u2019ll find a ready\u2011to\u2011go itinerary plus three hotel choices (budget / mid\u2011range / luxury) with nightly rates.\n\n---\n\n## DAY\u2011BY\u2011DAY ITINERARY  \n\n### **Day\u202f1 \u2013 Arrival, North\u2011Goa Highlights & Sunset Party**\n\n| Time | Activity | Details & Cost |\n|------|----------|----------------|\n| **08:00 \u2013 10:30** | **Travel to Goa** | Flight (e.g., IndiGo 6\u202fAM \u2013 08\u202fAM) \u2013 \u20b9\u202f3\u202f500 or Train (Mumbai\u202f\u2192\u202fMadgaon AC\u2011Chair) \u2013 \u20b9\u202f2\u202f200. |\n| **10:30 \u2013 11:00** | **Transfer to hotel** | Pre\u2011booked taxi (\u20b9\u202f600) to your chosen hotel in **Calangute/Baga** area. |\n| **11:00 \u2013 12:30** | **Check\u2011in & freshen up** | Drop luggage, quick shower. |\n| **12:30 \u2013 14:00** | **Lunch at Fisherman\u2019s Wharf (Calangute)** | Goan seafood thali \u2013 \u20b9\u202f500\u2011800. |\n| **14:00 \u2013 16:30** | **Beach time \u2013 Calangute & Baga** | Sunbathe, optional parasailing (\u20b9\u202f1\u202f200) or jet\u2011ski (\u20b9\u202f1\u202f500). |\n| **16:30 \u2013 18:00** | **Explore Fort Aguada & Lighthouse** | Entry free; small parking fee \u20b9\u202f30. |\n| **18:30 \u2013 20:00** | **Sunset at Candolim Beach** | Walk along the shore, grab a coconut water (\u20b9\u202f50). |\n| **20:30 \u2013 22:30** | **Dinner & Nightlife** | **Tito\u2019s Bar** (Baga) \u2013 Goan\u2011style pizza + drinks \u2013 \u20b9\u202f1\u202f200. |\n| **22:30** | **Return to hotel** | Rest for the night. |\n\n**Day\u20111 total (excluding accommodation):** ~\u20b9\u202f5\u202f500 \u2013 7\u202f000  \n\n---\n\n### **Day\u202f2 \u2013 South\u2011Goa Culture, Beach & Departure**\n\n| Time | Activity | Details & Cost |\n|------|----------|----------------|\n| **07:30 \u2013 08:30** | **Breakfast** | Hotel buffet (budget) \u2013 \u20b9\u202f250; mid\u2011range caf\u00e9 \u2013 \u20b9\u202f400; luxury resort \u2013 included. |\n| **08:30 \u2013 10:30** | **Drive to Old Goa** | Taxi/uber (\u20b9\u202f500) \u2013 visit **Basilica of Bom\u202fJesus** (free) & **Se Cathedral** (free). |\n| **10:30 \u2013 12:00** | **Museum of Christian Art** | Entry \u20b9\u202f30. |\n| **12:00 \u2013 13:30** | **Lunch at Mum\u2019s Kitchen (Panaji)** | Authentic Goan cuisine \u2013 \u20b9\u202f600\u2011900. |\n| **13:30 \u2013 15:00** | **Miramar Beach & Panaji promenade** | Relax, optional paddle\u2011boarding (\u20b9\u202f800). |\n| **15:00 \u2013 16:30** | **Shopping in Panaji Market** | Souvenirs, spices \u2013 budget \u20b9\u202f500\u20111\u202f000. |\n| **16:30 \u2013 17:30** | **Return to hotel, pack** | |\n| **17:30 \u2013 18:30** | **Early dinner / snack** | Beach shack (Goan fish curry rice) \u2013 \u20b9\u202f300\u2011500. |\n| **19:00** | **Check\u2011out & transfer to airport/railway station** | Taxi (\u20b9\u202f600). |\n| **21:00 \u2013 23:30** | **Flight/Train back home** | Same cost as inbound. |\n\n**Day\u20112 total (excluding accommodation):** ~\u20b9\u202f4\u202f500 \u2013 6\u202f500  \n\n---\n\n## HOTEL RECOMMENDATIONS  \n\n| Tier | Hotel (Location) | Nightly Rate (incl. taxes) | Amenities | Approx. 2\u2011Night Cost |\n|------|------------------|----------------------------|-----------|----------------------|\n| **Budget** | **Casa De Goa \u2013 Guesthouse** (Calangute) | **\u20b9\u202f2\u202f500** | Air\u2011cond rooms, free Wi\u2011Fi, rooftop lounge, 10\u2011min walk to beach | **\u20b9\u202f5\u202f000** |\n| | **The Fern Residency** (Baga) | \u20b9\u202f2\u202f800 | Swimming pool, garden, complimentary breakfast | \u20b9\u202f5\u202f600 |\n| **Mid\u2011range** | **Novotel Goa Resort & Spa** (Candolim) | **\u20b9\u202f6\u202f500** | Outdoor pool, spa, 2\u2011restaurant buffet, beach shuttle | **\u20b9\u202f13\u202f000** |\n| | **Casa De Goa \u2013 Boutique Hotel** (Panaji) | \u20b9\u202f7\u202f000 | Heritage d\u00e9cor, rooftop bar, free breakfast | \u20b9\u202f14\u202f000 |\n| **Luxury** | **Taj Exotica Resort & Spa** (Benaulim, South Goa) | **\u20b9\u202f18\u202f000** | Private beach, multiple pools, spa, 3\u2011restaurant complex, airport pick\u2011up | **\u20b9\u202f36\u202f000** |\n| | **Alila Diwa Goa** (Majorda) | \u20b9\u202f20\u202f000 | Infinity pool, yoga pavilion, fine\u2011dining, complimentary scooter | \u20b9\u202f40\u202f000 |\n\n*All hotels listed have 24\u2011hour front desk, safe\u2011deposit boxes, and easy access to the attractions in the itinerary. Prices are for a **double\u2011occupancy** room; single\u2011occupancy rates are roughly 10\u201115\u202f% higher.*\n\n---\n\n## BUDGET BREAKDOWN (Example Scenarios)\n\n### 1\ufe0f\u20e3 Budget\u2011Friendly Trip  \n| Item | Cost |\n|------|------|\n| Flights (round\u2011trip) | \u20b9\u202f3\u202f500 |\n| Airport\u2011to\u2011hotel taxi (both ways) | \u20b9\u202f1\u202f200 |\n| Scooter rental (2\u202fdays) | \u20b9\u202f800 |\n| Accommodation (Casa De Goa) | \u20b9\u202f5\u202f000 |\n| Food (local shacks & modest restaurants) | \u20b9\u202f2\u202f500 |\n| Attractions & water\u2011sports | \u20b9\u202f2\u202f000 |\n| Miscellaneous | \u20b9\u202f500 |\n| **Total** | **\u20b9\u202f15\u202f500** |\n\n> **You still have ~\u20b9\u202f34\u202f500** left for shopping, upgraded meals, or a splurge on a sunset cruise.\n\n---\n\n### 2\ufe0f\u20e3 Mid\u2011Range Comfort Trip  \n| Item | Cost |\n|------|------|\n| Flights (round\u2011trip) | \u20b9\u202f4\u202f500 |\n| Airport\u2011to\u2011hotel taxi | \u20b9\u202f1\u202f200 |\n| Uber/Taxi for 2\u202fdays | \u20b9\u202f1\u202f200 |\n| Accommodation (Novotel Goa) | \u20b9\u202f13\u202f000 |\n| Food (mix of mid\u2011range restaurants) | \u20b9\u202f4\u202f500 |\n| Attractions & water\u2011sports | \u20b9\u202f3\u202f500 |\n| Miscellaneous | \u20b9\u202f800 |\n| **Total** | **\u20b9\u202f28\u202f700** |\n\n> **Remaining budget \u2248\u202f\u20b9\u202f21\u202f300** \u2013 you could add a dolphin\u2011watching cruise (\u2248\u20b9\u202f2\u202f500) or upgrade to a luxury dinner.\n\n---\n\n### 3\ufe0f\u20e3 Luxury Escape Trip  \n| Item | Cost |\n|------|------|\n| Flights (premium carrier) | \u20b9\u202f9\u202f000 |\n| Airport\u2011to\u2011hotel private transfer | \u20b9\u202f2\u202f000 |\n| Luxury resort (Taj Exotica) | \u20b9\u202f36\u202f000 |\n| Food (all\u2011inclusive or \u00e0\u2011la\u2011carte at resort) | \u20b9\u202f6\u202f000 |\n| Premium activities (private yacht sunset cruise, spa) | \u20b9\u202f5\u202f000 |\n| Miscellaneous (souvenirs, tips) | \u20b9\u202f1\u202f000 |\n| **Total** | **\u20b9\u202f59\u202f000** |\n\n> **This exceeds the \u20b9\u202f50\u202f000 limit** by ~\u20b9\u202f9\u202f000. You can bring it down by:  \n> \u2022 Choosing a mid\u2011range hotel (saves ~\u20b9\u202f13\u202f000)  \n> \u2022 Flying economy instead of premium (saves ~\u20b9\u202f2\u202f000)  \n> \u2022 Selecting 1\u20112 premium activities instead of both.\n\n---\n\n## QUICK TIPS & LOCAL INSIGHTS  \n\n| Tip | Why it matters |\n|-----|-----------------|\n| **Book flights & hotels 2\u20113\u202fweeks in advance** | Prices drop 15\u201130\u202f% and you lock in the best rooms. |\n| **Rent a scooter** | Cheapest way to zip between beaches (\u20b9\u202f350\u2011400 per day). |\n| **Carry cash for beach shacks** | Many small vendors don\u2019t accept cards. |\n| **Stay hydrated** | Goa can be hot & humid; a 500\u202fml bottle costs ~\u20b9\u202f20. |\n| **Respect local culture** | Dress modestly when visiting churches and forts. |\n| **Nightlife safety** | Use reputable cabs (Ola/Uber) after dark; keep your drink in sight. |\n| **Best time to visit** | October\u2011March for pleasant weather and lower humidity. |\n\n---\n\n## FINAL RECOMMENDATION  \n\nGiven your **\u20b9\u202f50\u202f000** budget, the **mid\u2011range scenario** (Novotel Goa + comfortable meals + a few water\u2011sports) gives you a **balanced experience**\u2014good beach time, cultural visits, and a taste of Goa\u2019s nightlife\u2014while still leaving **\u2248\u202f\u20b9\u202f20\u202f000** for souvenirs, an optional dolphin\u2011watch cruise, or a special dinner at a beachfront restaurant.\n\n**If you\u2019d like a detailed booking list (flight numbers, exact hotel contact, or a custom day\u2011by\u2011day schedule with exact timings), just let me know and I\u2019ll send it over!**", "refusal": null, "role": "assistant", "annotations": null, "audio": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": null, "reasoning": "We need to produce a day-by-day itinerary for a two-day trip to Goa, with budget of 50,000 (presumably INR). Provide activities, hotel options (budget/mid/luxury with prices), and budget breakdown (accommodation, food, transport, attractions, total). Should be helpful. Provide suggestions for transport (flight/train, local transport). Provide cost estimates. Also note that 50,000 INR for two days is generous; can allocate accordingly.\n\nWe need to follow developer instruction: Travel Planner. Provide day-by-day itinerary, hotel options, budget breakdown.\n\nWe'll assume INR. Provide three categories: budget (\u20b92,000-3,000 per night), mid (\u20b95,000-7,000), luxury (\u20b912,000-20,000). Provide approximate costs.\n\nFood: budget (\u20b9300-500 per meal), mid (\u20b9800-1200), luxury (\u20b91500+). Provide daily totals.\n\nTransport: arrival (flight or train) cost estimate, local transport (rent scooter \u20b9350/day, taxi etc). Provide total.\n\nAttractions: entry fees.\n\nTotal budget: ensure within 50,000.\n\nWill present in table.\n\nLet's craft."}}], "created": 1771571104, "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b", "object": "chat.completion", "service_tier": "on_demand", "system_fingerprint": "fp_8a618bed98", "usage": {"completion_tokens": 2722, "prompt_tokens": 137, "total_tokens": 2859, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 246, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": null, "queue_time": 0.045700558, "prompt_time": 0.00521607, "completion_time": 5.910367505, "total_time": 5.915583575}, "usage_breakdown": null, "x_groq": {"id": "req_01khwxvcr3fqe8v7h50mjak3k7", "seed": 1077101650}}, "prompt_tokens": 137, "completion_tokens": 2722, "agent_id": "Travel_Planner_621271b9-8277-4364-8dc2-79d1bec1fa01/621271b9-8277-4364-8dc2-79d1bec1fa01"}
2026-02-20 12:35:01 - INFO - 405 -Publishing message of type GroupChatMessage to all subscribers: {'message': TextMessage(id='4a846d2c-626d-4cd6-aee3-c62dec908f4b', source='Travel_Planner', models_usage=RequestUsage(prompt_tokens=137, completion_tokens=2722), metadata={}, created_at=datetime.datetime(2026, 2, 20, 7, 5, 1, 96366, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), content='## 2\u2011Day Goa Getaway –\u202f\u20b9\u202f50\u202f000 (INR) Budget  \n*(All prices are approximate, per person, and shown in Indian Rupees)*  \n\n| Category | What’s Included | Approx. Cost (per person) |\n|----------|----------------|---------------------------|\n| **Flights / Train** | Round\u2011trip (Mumbai \u2194 Goa) – low\u2011cost airline or AC\u2011chair\u2011car train | **\u20b9\u202f6\u202f000 – 9\u202f000** |\n| **Airport\u2011/Rail\u2011to\u2011Hotel Transfer** | Pre\u2011booked taxi / app\u2011cab (\u224830\u202fkm) | **\u20b9\u202f800 – 1\u202f200** |\n| **Local Transport** | 2\u2011day scooter rental (incl. fuel) or 2\u2011day Uber/Taxi budget | **\u20b9\u202f800 – 1\u202f200** |\n| **Accommodation** | See three hotel tiers below (2 nights) | **\u20b9\u202f4\u202f000 – 40\u202f000** |\n| **Food & Drinks** | Breakfast, lunch, dinner + 2\u20113 drinks/snacks per day | **\u20b9\u202f2\u202f500 – 7\u202f500** |\n| **Attractions & Activities** | Beach entry, entry fees, water\u2011sports, entry to forts/museums, night\u2011life entry | **\u20b9\u202f2\u202f000 – 5\u202f000** |\n| **Miscellaneous** | Souvenirs, tips, emergency cash | **\u20b9\u202f500 – 1\u202f000** |\n| **Total** |  | **\u20b9\u202f16\u202f600 – 64\u202f900** |\n\n> **Bottom line:** Even the most luxurious option (\u20b9\u202f40\u202f000 for a 5\u2011star stay) stays well under the \u20b9\u202f50\u202f000 ceiling, leaving plenty of room for food, activities and a little shopping. Below you’ll find a ready\u2011to\u2011go itinerary plus three hotel choices (budget / mid\u2011range / luxury) with nightly rates.\n\n---\n\n## DAY\u2011BY\u2011DAY ITINERARY  \n\n### **Day\u202f1 – Arrival, North\u2011Goa Highlights & Sunset Party**\n\n| Time | Activity | Details & Cost |\n|------|----------|----------------|\n| **08:00 – 10:30** | **Travel to Goa** | Flight (e.g., IndiGo 6\u202fAM – 08\u202fAM) – \u20b9\u202f3\u202f500 or Train (Mumbai\u202f\u2192\u202fMadgaon AC\u2011Chair) – \u20b9\u202f2\u202f200. |\n| **10:30 – 11:00** | **Transfer to hotel** | Pre\u2011booked taxi (\u20b9\u202f600) to your chosen hotel in **Calangute/Baga** area. |\n| **11:00 – 12:30** | **Check\u2011in & freshen up** | Drop luggage, quick shower. |\n| **12:30 – 14:00** | **Lunch at Fisherman’s Wharf (Calangute)** | Goan seafood thali – \u20b9\u202f500\u2011800. |\n| **14:00 – 16:30** | **Beach time – Calangute & Baga** | Sunbathe, optional parasailing (\u20b9\u202f1\u202f200) or jet\u2011ski (\u20b9\u202f1\u202f500). |\n| **16:30 – 18:00** | **Explore Fort Aguada & Lighthouse** | Entry free; small parking fee \u20b9\u202f30. |\n| **18:30 – 20:00** | **Sunset at Candolim Beach** | Walk along the shore, grab a coconut water (\u20b9\u202f50). |\n| **20:30 – 22:30** | **Dinner & Nightlife** | **Tito’s Bar** (Baga) – Goan\u2011style pizza + drinks – \u20b9\u202f1\u202f200. |\n| **22:30** | **Return to hotel** | Rest for the night. |\n\n**Day\u20111 total (excluding accommodation):** ~\u20b9\u202f5\u202f500 – 7\u202f000  \n\n---\n\n### **Day\u202f2 – South\u2011Goa Culture, Beach & Departure**\n\n| Time | Activity | Details & Cost |\n|------|----------|----------------|\n| **07:30 – 08:30** | **Breakfast** | Hotel buffet (budget) – \u20b9\u202f250; mid\u2011range café – \u20b9\u202f400; luxury resort – included. |\n| **08:30 – 10:30** | **Drive to Old Goa** | Taxi/uber (\u20b9\u202f500) – visit **Basilica of Bom\u202fJesus** (free) & **Se Cathedral** (free). |\n| **10:30 – 12:00** | **Museum of Christian Art** | Entry \u20b9\u202f30. |\n| **12:00 – 13:30** | **Lunch at Mum’s Kitchen (Panaji)** | Authentic Goan cuisine – \u20b9\u202f600\u2011900. |\n| **13:30 – 15:00** | **Miramar Beach & Panaji promenade** | Relax, optional paddle\u2011boarding (\u20b9\u202f800). |\n| **15:00 – 16:30** | **Shopping in Panaji Market** | Souvenirs, spices – budget \u20b9\u202f500\u20111\u202f000. |\n| **16:30 – 17:30** | **Return to hotel, pack** | |\n| **17:30 – 18:30** | **Early dinner / snack** | Beach shack (Goan fish curry rice) – \u20b9\u202f300\u2011500. |\n| **19:00** | **Check\u2011out & transfer to airport/railway station** | Taxi (\u20b9\u202f600). |\n| **21:00 – 23:30** | **Flight/Train back home** | Same cost as inbound. |\n\n**Day\u20112 total (excluding accommodation):** ~\u20b9\u202f4\u202f500 – 6\u202f500  \n\n---\n\n## HOTEL RECOMMENDATIONS  \n\n| Tier | Hotel (Location) | Nightly Rate (incl. taxes) | Amenities | Approx. 2\u2011Night Cost |\n|------|------------------|----------------------------|-----------|----------------------|\n| **Budget** | **Casa De Goa – Guesthouse** (Calangute) | **\u20b9\u202f2\u202f500** | Air\u2011cond rooms, free Wi\u2011Fi, rooftop lounge, 10\u2011min walk to beach | **\u20b9\u202f5\u202f000** |\n| | **The Fern Residency** (Baga) | \u20b9\u202f2\u202f800 | Swimming pool, garden, complimentary breakfast | \u20b9\u202f5\u202f600 |\n| **Mid\u2011range** | **Novotel Goa Resort & Spa** (Candolim) | **\u20b9\u202f6\u202f500** | Outdoor pool, spa, 2\u2011restaurant buffet, beach shuttle | **\u20b9\u202f13\u202f000** |\n| | **Casa De Goa – Boutique Hotel** (Panaji) | \u20b9\u202f7\u202f000 | Heritage décor, rooftop bar, free breakfast | \u20b9\u202f14\u202f000 |\n| **Luxury** | **Taj Exotica Resort & Spa** (Benaulim, South Goa) | **\u20b9\u202f18\u202f000** | Private beach, multiple pools, spa, 3\u2011restaurant complex, airport pick\u2011up | **\u20b9\u202f36\u202f000** |\n| | **Alila Diwa Goa** (Majorda) | \u20b9\u202f20\u202f000 | Infinity pool, yoga pavilion, fine\u2011dining, complimentary scooter | \u20b9\u202f40\u202f000 |\n\n*All hotels listed have 24\u2011hour front desk, safe\u2011deposit boxes, and easy access to the attractions in the itinerary. Prices are for a **double\u2011occupancy** room; single\u2011occupancy rates are roughly 10\u201115\u202f% higher.*\n\n---\n\n## BUDGET BREAKDOWN (Example Scenarios)\n\n### 1\ufe0f\u20e3 Budget\u2011Friendly Trip  \n| Item | Cost |\n|------|------|\n| Flights (round\u2011trip) | \u20b9\u202f3\u202f500 |\n| Airport\u2011to\u2011hotel taxi (both ways) | \u20b9\u202f1\u202f200 |\n| Scooter rental (2\u202fdays) | \u20b9\u202f800 |\n| Accommodation (Casa De Goa) | \u20b9\u202f5\u202f000 |\n| Food (local shacks & modest restaurants) | \u20b9\u202f2\u202f500 |\n| Attractions & water\u2011sports | \u20b9\u202f2\u202f000 |\n| Miscellaneous | \u20b9\u202f500 |\n| **Total** | **\u20b9\u202f15\u202f500** |\n\n> **You still have ~\u20b9\u202f34\u202f500** left for shopping, upgraded meals, or a splurge on a sunset cruise.\n\n---\n\n### 2\ufe0f\u20e3 Mid\u2011Range Comfort Trip  \n| Item | Cost |\n|------|------|\n| Flights (round\u2011trip) | \u20b9\u202f4\u202f500 |\n| Airport\u2011to\u2011hotel taxi | \u20b9\u202f1\u202f200 |\n| Uber/Taxi for 2\u202fdays | \u20b9\u202f1\u202f200 |\n| Accommodation (Novotel Goa) | \u20b9\u202f13\u202f000 |\n| Food (mix of mid\u2011range restaurants) | \u20b9\u202f4\u202f500 |\n| Attractions & water\u2011sports | \u20b9\u202f3\u202f500 |\n| Miscellaneous | \u20b9\u202f800 |\n| **Total** | **\u20b9\u202f28\u202f700** |\n\n> **Remaining budget \u2248\u202f\u20b9\u202f21\u202f300** – you could add a dolphin\u2011watching cruise (\u2248\u20b9\u202f2\u202f500) or upgrade to a luxury dinner.\n\n---\n\n### 3\ufe0f\u20e3 Luxury Escape Trip  \n| Item | Cost |\n|------|------|\n| Flights (premium carrier) | \u20b9\u202f9\u202f000 |\n| Airport\u2011to\u2011hotel private transfer | \u20b9\u202f2\u202f000 |\n| Luxury resort (Taj Exotica) | \u20b9\u202f36\u202f000 |\n| Food (all\u2011inclusive or ŕ\u2011la\u2011carte at resort) | \u20b9\u202f6\u202f000 |\n| Premium activities (private yacht sunset cruise, spa) | \u20b9\u202f5\u202f000 |\n| Miscellaneous (souvenirs, tips) | \u20b9\u202f1\u202f000 |\n| **Total** | **\u20b9\u202f59\u202f000** |\n\n> **This exceeds the \u20b9\u202f50\u202f000 limit** by ~\u20b9\u202f9\u202f000. You can bring it down by:  \n> • Choosing a mid\u2011range hotel (saves ~\u20b9\u202f13\u202f000)  \n> • Flying economy instead of premium (saves ~\u20b9\u202f2\u202f000)  \n> • Selecting 1\u20112 premium activities instead of both.\n\n---\n\n## QUICK TIPS & LOCAL INSIGHTS  \n\n| Tip | Why it matters |\n|-----|-----------------|\n| **Book flights & hotels 2\u20113\u202fweeks in advance** | Prices drop 15\u201130\u202f% and you lock in the best rooms. |\n| **Rent a scooter** | Cheapest way to zip between beaches (\u20b9\u202f350\u2011400 per day). |\n| **Carry cash for beach shacks** | Many small vendors don’t accept cards. |\n| **Stay hydrated** | Goa can be hot & humid; a 500\u202fml bottle costs ~\u20b9\u202f20. |\n| **Respect local culture** | Dress modestly when visiting churches and forts. |\n| **Nightlife safety** | Use reputable cabs (Ola/Uber) after dark; keep your drink in sight. |\n| **Best time to visit** | October\u2011March for pleasant weather and lower humidity. |\n\n---\n\n## FINAL RECOMMENDATION  \n\nGiven your **\u20b9\u202f50\u202f000** budget, the **mid\u2011range scenario** (Novotel Goa + comfortable meals + a few water\u2011sports) gives you a **balanced experience**—good beach time, cultural visits, and a taste of Goa’s nightlife—while still leaving **\u2248\u202f\u20b9\u202f20\u202f000** for souvenirs, an optional dolphin\u2011watch cruise, or a special dinner at a beachfront restaurant.\n\n**If you’d like a detailed booking list (flight numbers, exact hotel contact, or a custom day\u2011by\u2011day schedule with exact timings), just let me know and I’ll send it over!**', type='TextMessage')}
